On the third day of the 2nd BSCF Astronomy Camp 2025, participants attended a Black Holes Insight Session led by Professor Saleh Hasan Naqib, Vice-Chancellor of Rajshahi University and Camp Adviser. The session provided a clear and engaging overview of black holes, exploring their formation, properties, and significance in the cosmos. Professor Naqib’s explanations were designed to inspire curiosity and deepen understanding among young astronomy enthusiasts. Following the presentation, a dynamic Q&A segment allowed participants to ask questions, discuss concepts, and share ideas about one of the universe’s most mysterious phenomena. The interactive discussion encouraged critical thinking, curiosity, and collaborative learning, making complex astronomical concepts accessible and exciting. The session successfully combined knowledge, engagement, and inspiration, leaving participants motivated to continue exploring space and developing their understanding of astronomy, while fostering a passion for science and discovery in a supportive and educational environment. 
